                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The chimera breathes a cone or line that deals [[/r 9d6 # damage]] damage to all creatures in the area (<span data-pf2-check=\"basic\" data-pf2-dc=\"26\" data-pf2-traits=\"arcane,evocation,damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"Breath Weapon DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic</span> save of a type indicated below). The color of the chimera's dragon head determines the area of the Breath Weapon, the type of damage it deals, and the type of save to avoid it. The chimera can't use Breath Weapon again for 1d4 rounds.<br /></p><ul><li><strong>Black</strong> 60-foot line of acid (Reflex)</li><li><strong>Blue</strong> 60-foot line of electricity (Reflex)</li><li><strong>Green</strong> 30-foot cone of poison (Fortitude)</li><li><strong>Red</strong> 30-foot cone of fire (Reflex)</li><li><strong>White</strong> 30-foot cone of cold (Reflex)</li></ul>"
